714146f-a.title: Manhattan: 63rd Street - Central Park West
714146f-a.text:
#1
63rd Street, north side, west from Central Park West. Brown stone fronts will be demolished to make place for the
Y.M.C.A
October 14,1927.
F.L.Sperr.

#2
Showing the new Y.M.C.A. at this location, as seen from across
the demolition of the Century Theatre.
January 23, 1931.
F.L. Sperr.

718447f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 63rd Street
718447f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, from 64th to 63rd Streets. The building with the flag, in left centre background, houses the Society for Ethical Culture School. At the extreme left is shown a portion of the Century Theatre (1909-1930).
March 11, 1929.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.

(2)
